      <h1>"Indian Ayurveda embodies centuries of wisdom, offering holistic health solutions rooted in nature. Its time-tested remedies promote vitality, balance, and well-being, enriching lives with profound care and ancient knowledge."
      </h1>
      
    </div>
    <div class="img-5">
        <div class ="box9">
  
        <table>
          
          <tr>
              <td>Turmeric (Curcuma longa):<br>

                Known for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.
                Helps in improving digestion, relieving joint pain, and supporting healthy skin.</td>
              <td>Tulsi (Holy Basil, Ocimum sanctum):<br>

                Considered sacred in India, tulsi is known for its medicinal properties.
                Supports respiratory health, helps in relieving cough and cold, and promotes stress relief.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td>Triphala:<br>

                A combination of three fruits: Amalaki (Emblica officinalis), Bibhitaki (Terminalia bellirica), and Haritaki (Terminalia chebula).
                Supports digestion, detoxification, and maintains overall gastrointestinal health.</td>
              <td>Shankhpushpi: <br> Enhances memory, aids cognitive function, and promotes mental clarity and focus</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td>Ginger (Zingiber officinale):<br>

                Aids digestion, reduces nausea, and has anti-inflammatory properties.
                Helps in relieving menstrual discomfort and supports immune function.</td>
              <td>Amla (Indian Gooseberry, Emblica officinalis):<br>

                Rich in vitamin C and antioxidants, supports immune function and promotes healthy skin and hair.
                Helps in managing acidity and supports digestion.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td>Jatamansi: <br>Calms the mind, reduces stress, and supports restful sleep and emotional balance.</td>
              <td>Amalaki (Indian Gooseberry): <br>Bursting with vitamin C, Amalaki fortifies immunity, combats free radicals, and nurtures health from within, contributing to radiant vitality and longevity.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td>Haritaki (Terminalia chebula): <br> Acting as nature's broom, Haritaki sweeps away toxins, supports smooth digestion, and relieves constipation, fostering a clean, balanced internal environment for optimal health.</td>
              <td>Bhringraj: <br> Revered for its hair-nourishing properties, Bhringraj stimulates hair growth, strengthens roots, and soothes the scalp, fostering luscious locks and vibrant hair health.</td>
          </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Khadira (Acacia catechu): <br>Supports oral health, treats mouth ulcers, and prevents gum diseases.</td>
            <td>Kutaja (Holarrhena antidysenterica): <br>Treats diarrhea, dysentery, and gastrointestinal infections with its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Vacha (Acorus calamus):<br> Improves concentration, aids digestion, and treats respiratory ailments like asthma and bronchitis.</td>
            <td>Mandukaparni (Centella asiatica):<br> Enhances brain function, boosts memory, and aids in managing anxiety and depression.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Pippali (Long Pepper): <br>Improves digestion, enhances metabolism, and supports respiratory health with its expectorant properties.

              </td>
            <td>Kantakari (Solanum xanthocarpum):<br> Treats respiratory disorders like asthma, bronchitis, and cough, acting as a bronchodilator.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Ashoka (Saraca asoca): <br>Treats gynecological disorders like menstrual irregularities, menorrhagia, and dysmenorrhea, and supports reproductive health.

              
             
              </td>
            <td>Manjistha (Rubia cordifolia):<br> Detoxifies the blood, treats skin disorders like acne, eczema, and psoriasis, and supports lymphatic circulation.
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td> Kumari (Aloe vera):<br> Treats skin disorders like burns, wounds, and dermatitis, and supports digestive health and immunity.
            </td>
            <td>Tagar (Valeriana wallichii):<br> Treats insomnia, anxiety, and nervous disorders, and promotes relaxation and restful sleep.</td>
        </tr>
